    <td width="402" valign="top"><p><strong><em>RATIONALE</em></strong></p>
      <p>An assessment is required to establish a baseline. Baselines are    important to CSI to assist in determining progress and if the goals of the    improvement initiatives have been achieved. </p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="154" valign="top"><p><strong><em>MOST CORRECT (5)</em></strong></p></td>
    <td width="45" valign="top"><p>D</p></td>
    <td width="402" valign="top"><p>Although the definitions and scope of improvements for establishing a    baseline are unknown, the best recommendation is that it must be a full assessment.    Expending the extra effort for a full assessment ensures that all areas that    will be improved in the future already have a baseline to start measuring    from. Such an assessment should cover the processes; the technologies used to    support and enable the processes, management reporting, people’s skills, and    the culture of the organization. </p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="154" valign="top"><p><strong><em>SECOND BEST (3)</em></strong></p></td>
    <td width="45" valign="top"><p>B</p></td>
    <td width="402" valign="top"><p>This answer lacks the important factor of reviewing the culture    (people) within the organization. Culture could be a particularly important factor    within the scope of the assessment to understand why there is some    misalignment between the business and IT. </p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="154" valign="top"><p><strong><em>THIRD BEST (1)</em></strong></p></td>
    <td width="45" valign="top"><p>C</p></td>
    <td width="402" valign="top"><p>While self-assessments can be useful to understand where performance    is, it is certainly not just those managers that have gone through    certification that could view their maturity. The answer does not make it    clear which assessment will be used, but most will be intuitive for those    with a sound level of knowledge of the organization. This answer is only    marginally better than answer “A”. </p></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="154" valign="top"><p><strong><em>DISTRACTER (0)</em></strong></p></td>
    <td width="45" valign="top"><p>A</p></td>
    <td width="402" valign="top"><p>This answer is obviously incorrect. In order to establish a proper    baseline it is important to look at more than just the processes. The    technology used to support and enable the processes is required as is an    assessment of the culture of the organization. </p></td>
  </tr>
